"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is prone to overflow errors because the factorial of 21 is a very large number that may exceed the fixed size of NumPy numeric types. The sample value of the variable (51090942171709440000) also indicates that the intermediate result of factorial(21) is too large for the NumPy numeric type.\",\n  \"patch\": \"1c1\\n< import numpy as np\\n---\\n> import numpy as np\\n> import math\\n2c2\\n< from math import factorial\\n---\\n> \\n3a4\\n> # Use math.log to calculate the logarithm of the factorial\\n> # This approach avoids the overflow error by not calculating the factorial directly\\n4c5\\n< print(np.log(factorial(21)))\\n---\\n> print(sum(np.log(np.arange(1, 22))))\\n\"\n}"